LEGIONELLOSIS - AUSTRALIA (VICTORIA)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 1998 21:19:26 WST
Source: The West Australian Newspaper, JULY 10th. 1998
Via: Denis Green <snoigel@hotmail.com>

Melbourne, Victoria
Victoria`s chief health officer yesterday issued a warning about the risks
of Legionnaires Disease after one women died from the disease and two
others were treated in hospital.
_Legionella_ bacteria were found in cooling towers near [a local] shopping
centre and two office blocks.
--
Denis Green
Research and Development Director
Tower San Systems
Perth, WA
